The paper introduces a new method for temporal learning and prediction, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on learning and prediction suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The use of networks and interrelated predictions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of predictive state representations, which suggests that it may also be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
